abstract: While waiting to hear from his most loyal backers, Mayor Bill de Blasio’s re-election campaign has been focusing on new contributors and smaller donations.
snippet: While waiting to hear from his most loyal backers, Mayor Bill de Blasio’s re-election campaign has been focusing on new contributors and smaller donations.
lead_paragraph: The big donors who helped sweep Mayor Bill de Blasio into office have largely been staying away from his re-election campaign.

abstract: Ms. McFarland’s departure has been seen as likely since the forced resignation of Michael T. Flynn. She may be nominated to be the United States ambassador to Singapore.
snippet: Ms. McFarland’s departure has been seen as likely since the forced resignation of Michael T. Flynn. She may be nominated to be the United States ambassador to Singapore.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — K. T. McFarland, the former Fox News commentator appointed by President Trump as deputy national security adviser, is expected to leave that position soon and may be nominated to be the United States ambassador to Singapore, according to officials briefed on the matter.

headline_main: K.T. McFarland, Deputy National Security Adviser, Is Expected to Leave Post
headline_print_headline: No. 2 Adviser  on Security  Is Expected to Leave Post

abstract: Those running for the post once held by Ken Thompson, who died last year, are promising to build on his work to change the criminal justice system.
snippet: Those running for the post once held by Ken Thompson, who died last year, are promising to build on his work to change the criminal justice system.
lead_paragraph: In February, as Eric Gonzalez, the acting Brooklyn district attorney, was getting ready to run for a four-year term, he sent out a news release hinting at how he might conduct his campaign.

abstract: President Trump and Senator Elizabeth Warren, a Democrat harshly critical of Wall Street, may both favor separating retail and investment banking.
snippet: President Trump and Senator Elizabeth Warren, a Democrat harshly critical of Wall Street, may both favor separating retail and investment banking.
lead_paragraph: President Trump has vowed to roll back financial regulation, saying that it is preventing banks from lending and businesses from growing.

abstract: Closing New York’s main jail complex to put correctional facilities around the city is a tough sell politically. But it could be an improvement for criminal justice and no impediment to new condos.
snippet: Closing New York’s main jail complex to put correctional facilities around the city is a tough sell politically. But it could be an improvement for criminal justice and no impediment to new condos.
lead_paragraph: Of the 2.3 million people confined to correctional facilities in the United States, close to 650,000 are in local jails, rather than state or federal prisons, and less than a third have been convicted of anything. In theory, jail stays are intended to be short, but the excruciating pace of bureaucracy means that the accused, many of whom cannot afford bail, might end up behind bars for months or years before their cases reach resolution and they are sent, or not sent, to prison.
